Hi @ShovanDhara!

I deleted the last reply since it was only the content of the tablesorter file. What I actually meant is that I wanted to see the code used to load and initialize tablesorter.

So somewhere in the `<head>`, tablesorter should be loaded:

```html
<!-- jQuery -->
<script src="js/jquery-latest.min.js"></script>
<!-- Tablesorter: required -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/theme.blue.css">
<script src="js/jquery.tablesorter.js"></script>
<script src="js/jquery.tablesorter.widgets.js"></script>
```

Then the code to initialize it should looks something like this:

```html
<script>
$(function(){
    $('#myTable').tablesorter({
        /* tablesorter options */
    });
});
</script>
```

Maybe it would be better if we communicated directly on the `#tablesorter` irc channel on freenode.net.

Hi @Chealer!

The [filter widget *options*](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#Widget-options) are included on detail on the main documentation page. More details about specific class names, methods, events and how to modify localization are found on the main ["filter widget" page](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-filter.html). Because of duplication, the filter widget page options are not as detailed as the documentation on the main documentation page.

To answer your question, you can disable filters for specific columns by adding a "filter-false" class to the column ([ref](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-filter.html#classes)). This will still add a filter, but it will be disabled. To completely hide the filter, you'll need to include some extra css:

```css
.tablesorter-filter.disabled {
  display: none;
}
```

For future reference, please don't open issues to ask a question. You can use Gitter, IRC or stackoverflow -  the links can be found in the [readme](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter#questions) on the main repo page.

