@rob-c I'm afraid it's still a syncing bug in Core. I hadn't seen it on develop branch with the Local backend but if you run a Dirac job, the job submits fine but ~50% of the time, (possibly if you don't restart Ganga before hand and it's an Exe+Dirac job) when the job completes, the completing messages go through with an additional warning of 'User changed status from submitted -> running' or something but you do 'jobs' and it still reports submitted. Restart ganga and it's all OK and the job completes again properly.

As I say, I hadn't seen this on the Local backend but certainly a few users running off CVMFS on CernVM saw a similar thing for Local Exe jobs, usually involving job copies, but the job would submit, complete and then if you do 'jobs' it still reports as new. 

